      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate strength sampled from lot-specific distributions (n=10 coupons). Rod diameter and screw thread geometry characterized via CMM on 5 components. Input uncertainties propagated via 500-sample Latin hypercube Monte Carlo yielding 95% prediction intervals on all three QoIs. The UQ characterizes total output variance attributable to the joint input distribution; identification of which individual inputs are dominant drivers is deferred to a planned sensitivity analysis extension. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
